def findhistogrammpeak(values, bins):
    
    v = np.where(values == values.max())
    most_frequent_value = np.round(bins[v], 0)
    
    return most_frequent_value

# 2D Function
def autoThresholding(image2d,
                     method='global_otsu',
                     radius = 10,
                     value=50):
    
    # calculate global Otsu threshold
    if method=='global_otsu':
        thresh = threshold_otsu(image2d)
        binary = image2D > thresh
    
    # claculate local Otsu threshold
    if method=='local_otsu':
        thresh = rank.otsu(image2D, disk(radius))
        binary = image2d > thresh
        
    if method=='value_based':
        binary = image2d > value
    
    return binary

# display original image subset

xmin, xmax = dtype_range[array.dtype.type]

# Display histogram and return values
values, bins, bars = ax[1].hist(array.ravel(), bins=bins)
# find the index for the highest values
v = np.where(values == values.max())
# get the most frequent pixel value
most_frequent_value = findhistogrammpeak(values, bins)
luminosity = np.round(most_frequent_value / 255 * 100, 0)

ax[1].ticklabel_format(axis='y', style='scientific', scilimits=(0, 0))
ax[1].set_xlabel('Pixel intensity')
ax[1].set_xlim(xmin, xmax)

# define relative threshold - default = 65%
th_rel = 0.75
threshold = np.round(most_frequent_value * th_rel, 0)

# Display cumulative distribution
ax1 = ax[1].twinx()
ax1.vlines(most_frequent_value, 0, 1, colors='r', linestyles='solid', lw=5, label='Max. Value')
ax1.vlines(threshold, 0, 1, colors='g', linestyles='solid', lw=5, label='abs. threshold')

image_label_overlay = label2rgb(img_label, image=array, bg_label=0)

fig, ax_label = plt.subplots(figsize=(16, 16))
ax_label.imshow(image_label_overlay)

sizeclasses = [5, 20, 50, 100, 500]
sizecolors = ['red', 'green', 'blue', 'yellow', 'cyan']
offset = 10
drawrect = True

particles = {}

for region in regionprops(img_label):
    
    for sc, c in zip(sizeclasses, sizecolors):
    
        # take regions with large enough areas
        if region.area >= sc: 

            properties = {}
            properties['Class'] = sc
            properties['Area'] = region.area
            properties['Major_Axis_Length'] = np.round(region.major_axis_length, 3)
            properties['Minor_Axis_Length'] = np.round(region.minor_axis_length, 3)
            #properties['Coords']=region.coords
            properties['Perimeter'] = np.round(region.perimeter, 3)
            properties['Solidity'] = np.round(region.solidity, 3)
            if region.minor_axis_length > 0:
                properties['RatioMinorMajor']=np.round(region.major_axis_length/region.minor_axis_length, 3)
            else:
                properties['RatioMinorMajor']= np.NaN
            
            particles[str(region.label)]=properties
            
            if drawrect:
                # draw rectangle around segmented particles and make the bounding recarngle bigger
                minr, minc, maxr, maxc = region.bbox
                minr = minr - offset
                maxr = maxr + offset
                minc = minc - offset
                maxc = maxc + offset
                rect = mpatches.Rectangle((minc, minr), maxc - minc, maxr - minr,
                                          fill=False,
                                          edgecolor=c,
                                          linewidth=2,
                                          label=str(sc) if str(sc) not in plt.gca().get_legend_handles_labels()[1] else '')

                ax_label.add_patch(rect)
            
#ax_label.set_axis_off()
ax_label.legend(loc='upper left')
#plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
